column4: anyone know how to get the sbs module loaded for lm-sensors, or what it is exactly? I have the same problem as http://ubuntuforums.org/showthread.php?t=1537746
injects modules into the kernel.  Think of it as 'turning a drive ron'
doesn't do anthing, modprobe -l doesnt show it, locate doesn't show it...
If it returns without giving an error that means it was inserted successfully.  Try running sudo sensors-detect
but modprobe -l should show it, shouldn't it??
Yeah it should.  Try lsmod | grep sbs
Does sudo sensors-detect work any differently?
What is the ultimate goal here?
get gkrellm to show all the sensors that are in the computer ...
Ignoring this sbs error what functionality are you getting out of gkrellm ?
shows quite a few sensors that the sensors command shows as well
I'm not sure what sbs does.  What the error pertains to.  Perhaps it makes no difference having it installed or not.  I can't offer any more advice :(
In short, if I were you I'd be in here asking people :P
ok, thanks all the same... there's no answer in #linux-sensors which is the lm-sensors channel here
Most channels are not as active as this one.  wait a while
